1. CREATE
To add a new document (a user in this case), you use the insertOne() method:

javascript
Copy
Edit
db.users.insertOne({
  name: "Alice",
  email: "alice@example.com",
  age: 28,
  isActive: true
});
You can also insert multiple users at once with insertMany():

javascript
Copy
Edit
db.users.insertMany([
  { name: "Bob", email: "bob@example.com", age: 35 },
  { name: "Carol", email: "carol@example.com", age: 24 }
]);
2. READ
To retrieve documents, you use find():

javascript
Copy
Edit
db.users.find(); // Returns all users
To filter results:

javascript
Copy
Edit
db.users.find({ age: { $gt: 30 } }); // Users older than 30
To format the results nicely:

javascript
Copy
Edit
db.users.find().pretty();
3. UPDATE
To update a userâ€™s information, use updateOne():

javascript
Copy
Edit
db.users.updateOne(
  { name: "Alice" },
  { $set: { age: 29, isActive: false } }
);
To update multiple users:

javascript
Copy
Edit
db.users.updateMany(
  { isActive: false },
  { $set: { status: "inactive" } }
);
You can also use operators like $inc to increment values:

javascript
Copy
Edit
db.users.updateOne(
  { name: "Bob" },
  { $inc: { age: 1 } }
);
4. DELETE
To remove a single document:

javascript
Copy
Edit
db.users.deleteOne({ name: "Carol" });
Or remove many:

javascript
Copy
Edit
db.users.deleteMany({ isActive: false });
